import qiskit
import numpy as np
from qiskit import QuantumCircuit, QuantumRegister, ClassicalRegister
from qiskit.visualization import plot_histogram, plot_bloch_multivector
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Set the number of qubits and the circuit depth
num_qubits = 2
depth = 5

# Create a quantum circuit with the desired number of qubits
q = QuantumRegister(num_qubits)
c = ClassicalRegister(num_qubits)
circuit = QuantumCircuit(q, c)

# Generate random parameters for the RY and RX gates
params = np.random.random((depth, num_qubits*2))

# Iterate over the circuit depth and qubits
for i in range(depth):
    for j in range(num_qubits):
        # Apply the RY and RX gates to the j-th qubit
        circuit.ry(params[i, j], q[j])
        circuit.rx(params[i, j + num_qubits], q[j])
        circuit.barrier(q)
        # Apply the Hadamard gate to both qubits
        circuit.h(q[0])
        circuit.h(q[1])
        
        # Apply a controlled-Z gate with the first qubit as the control and the second qubit as the target
        circuit.cz(q[0], q[1])

        # Apply phase shifts to the first and second qubits
        circuit.p(np.pi/2, q[0])
        circuit.p(np.pi/4, q[1])

        # Apply the Hadamard gate to both qubits again
        circuit.h(q[0])
        circuit.h(q[1])

# Measure both qubits
circuit.measure(q, c)
# Draw the circuit using Matplotlib
circuit.draw(output='mpl')
